<HEAD>Missing Act Of Donizetti Opera Found in Cellar</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The missing second act of an opera by Italian composer <PERSON> Gaetano </PERSON> <PERSON> Donizetti </PERSON> has been found in the cellar of the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Opera </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>, four years after an <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> musicologist discovered its first and third acts there, the Sunday Times reported. The lost portion of the three-act `` <PERSON> Elisabeth </PERSON>'' was discovered last week by Australian conductor <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Bonynge </PERSON>. He is currently leading his wife, <PERSON> Dame </PERSON> <PERSON> Joan </PERSON> <PERSON> Sutherland </PERSON>, in a production of <PERSON> Donizetti </PERSON>'s `` <PERSON> Anna </PERSON> <PERSON> Bolena </PERSON>'' at the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Opera </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> at Covent Garden. The Times quoted him as saying he made the discovery `` absolutely by chance, in an old stack of ballet rubbish -LRB- music -RRB-.'' <PERSON> Donizetti </PERSON>, who was born in 1797 and died in 1848, composed the work in 1838. The opera, set in <LOCATION> Russia </LOCATION>, tells the story of a young woman's walk from <LOCATION> Siberia </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> to try to win her father's freedom from exile `` Elisabeth'' first surfaced four years ago when <PERSON> Will </PERSON> <PERSON> Crutchfield </PERSON>, an <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> musicologist, found the first and third acts. It is n't known how the score of the music got to Covent Garden. The fact that the pages are singed indicates it may have been near a fire, possibly one that broke out at the opera house in 1856 or one 11 years later at Her Majesty's Theater, to which <PERSON> Donizetti </PERSON> had unsuccessfully offered the work. `` We are now looking for the first possible opportunity to bring this opera before the ublic _ it will probably be within 18 months and init