<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The leader of <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Roman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> on Sunday criticized political restrictions and <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> economic sanctions, saying the crisis `` weighs heavily on the smallest people.'' Speaking at the traditional Corpus Christi Mass held this year in an open field and attended by nearly 40,000 people, Archbishop <PERSON> Marcos </PERSON> <PERSON> Gregorio </PERSON> <PERSON> McGrath </PERSON> urged <LOCATION> Panamanian </LOCATION> political leaders to resolve the dispute. He said their actions `` will determine the future of this country for generations to come.'' The <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration imposed economic sanctions against <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> after Gen. <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, commander of the <ORGANIZATION> Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Forces </ORGANIZATION>, was indicted in February by federal grand juries in <LOCATION> Florifa </LOCATION> that accused him of drug trafficking. <PERSON> Noriega </PERSON>, who controls the civilian government, has rejected <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> efforts to make him resign and leave the country. <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> uses the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dollar as its currency and the sanctions have brought economic stagnation and increasing unemployment. People attending the Mass stood under a multicolored cover of thousands of umbrellas for the service by <PERSON> McGrath </PERSON> and other members of the Panamanian conference of bishops. The archbishop pleaded for an end to what he called `` political restrictions inside and economic restrictions from abroad.'' He also said negotiations to solve the crisis `` must be in <LOCATION> Panama </LOCATION> and among Panamanians with the respect among the parties that is required by any dialogue.'' <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials have been in