<LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Fuller </PERSON>, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s chief of staff, told reporters, `` <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> recognizes the importance of environmental and quality of life issues in <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>.'' <PERSON> Fuller </PERSON> said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> was advocating the delay `` until next year giving his secretary of the interior an opportunity to study the matter and determine whether or not to go further.'' However, he said, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> opposes `` an absolute moratorium'' like the one called for by <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> spoke at the dedication of the methanol pump at an <ORGANIZATION> ARCO </ORGANIZATION> station at <LOCATION> Wilshire </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Hobart </LOCATION> boulevards. `` A strong domestic energy industry is essential to our national security, and I am one who believes we've got strengthen the overall energy base of this country and protect the environment at the same time,'' he said. He acknowledged that `` sometimes these goals seem incompatible as with the current concern about offshore drilling. `` I was one of the pioneers in the equipment end of offshore drilling in the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> and I know it can be done safely. But there are other considerations _ tourism, marine life, aesthetics _ and in some extraordinarily sensitive areas, those considerations may prevail.''
