would serve as hosts. The negotiations would be aimed at self-rule for 1.5 million Palestinian Arabs in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION>, but not a separate state. In a second stage, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and the Arabs would try to find an overall settlement to their conflict.
